    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An allotropic form of carbon material derived from graphite consisting of sheets one atom thick arranged in a two-dimensional honeycomb lattice. It has exceptionally high tensile strength, electrical conductivity, transparency, and is the thinnest two-dimensional material known.</Note_Text>
